---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<BaseHead title="About — June" description="UX and product designer specialising in information-dense, decision-critical products." />
</head>
<body>
	<div class="cursor" id="cursor"></div>
	<div class="cursor-ring" id="ring"></div>

	<Header />

	<div class="page-wrapper">

		<!-- ── Side nav (RIGHT) ── -->
		<div class="side-nav-col">
			<nav class="side-nav" id="sideNav">
				<div class="side-nav-group">
					<a class="side-nav-item active" href="#s-intro">Intro</a>
					<a class="side-nav-item" href="#s-interests">Interests</a>
					<a class="side-nav-item" href="#s-philosophy">Design Philosophy</a>
					<a class="side-nav-item" href="#s-experience">Experience</a>
					<a class="side-nav-item" href="#s-education">Education</a>
					<a class="side-nav-item" href="#s-skills">Skills</a>
				</div>
			</nav>
		</div>

		<!-- ── Main content ── -->
		<div class="main-content">

			<!-- HERO -->
			<section class="hero" id="s-intro">
				<div class="hero-eyebrow">
					<div class="hero-eyebrow-line"></div>
					<span>About</span>
				</div>
				<div class="hero-grid">
					<div class="hero-left">
						<img src="/images/nannan.png" alt="me and my cat nannan" class="hero-avatar" />
						<span class="hero-img-caption">me and my cat nannan</span>
					</div>
					<div class="hero-right">
						<div>
							<h1 class="hero-name"><em>June</em> Fang</h1>
							<div class="hero-title-line">Product Designer</div>
						</div>
						<div class="hero-bio-block">
							<p class="hero-bio">I'm a UX designer who zooms out before zooming in.</p>
							<p class="hero-bio">I believe good design starts with the right question, not the right solution. I like to understand the full picture first, then care deeply about every detail that follows.</p>
						</div>
						<div>
							<div class="contact-row">
								<span class="contact-label">Location</span>
								<span class="contact-value">Berkeley, CA</span>
							</div>
							<div class="contact-row">
								<span class="contact-label">Email</span>
								<a href="mailto:juef@berkeley.edu" class="contact-value">juef@berkeley.edu</a>
							</div>
							<div class="contact-row">
								<span class="contact-label">Phone</span>
								<a href="tel:+16267163616" class="contact-value">+1 626 716 3616</a>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- INTERESTS -->
			<section class="section reveal" id="s-interests">
				<div class="section-head">
					<span class="section-title">Outside of Work</span>
					<span class="section-tag">Interests</span>
				</div>
				<div class="interests-grid">
					<div class="interest-card" data-hover-img="/images/golf.jpg">
						<div class="interest-icon">⛳</div>
						<div class="interest-title">Golf</div>
						<p class="interest-text">There is something about golf that mirrors good design. The feedback loop is immediate, the margin for error is small, and the only way to improve is deliberate repetition. Still chasing a sub-80 round.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="interest-card" data-hover-img="/images/hiking.jpg">
						<div class="interest-icon">🏔</div>
						<div class="interest-title">Hiking</div>
						<p class="interest-text">Trail time is thinking time. Some of the clearest design ideas happen away from the screen, somewhere on an incline with no reception. The Bay Area trails have been good for both the legs and the ideas.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- PHILOSOPHY -->
			<section class="section reveal" id="s-philosophy">
				<div class="section-head">
					<span class="section-title">Design Philosophy</span>
					<span class="section-tag">How I think about design</span>
				</div>
				<div class="philosophy-grid">
					<div class="philosophy-card">
						<div class="philosophy-num">01</div>
						<div class="philosophy-title">Complexity is the raw material. Clarity is the product.</div>
						<p class="philosophy-text">The hardest part of design is not making things look good. It is understanding a system deeply enough to know what can be removed. Every layer of unnecessary complexity is a decision someone else has to make on behalf of the user.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="philosophy-card">
						<div class="philosophy-num">02</div>
						<div class="philosophy-title">Design for the decision, not the screen.</div>
						<p class="philosophy-text">Every interface is a series of moments where someone has to decide something. I start there, mapping the decision before I design the UI. The best interfaces make people feel more capable, not just more informed.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="philosophy-card">
						<div class="philosophy-num">03</div>
						<div class="philosophy-title">Domain knowledge is a design tool.</div>
						<p class="philosophy-text">You cannot design well for what you do not understand. Before any wireframe, I learn the domain: the language, the constraints, the stakes. Empathy without expertise produces solutions that feel right but fail in practice.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="philosophy-card">
						<div class="philosophy-num">04</div>
						<div class="philosophy-title">The right friction is invisible. The wrong friction is everything.</div>
						<p class="philosophy-text">Not all friction is bad. Some decisions deserve to feel deliberate. The job is knowing which moments need speed and which need pause, and designing each one with intention.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- EXPERIENCE -->
			<section class="section reveal" id="s-experience">
				<div class="section-head">
					<span class="section-title">Experience</span>
					<span class="section-tag">2022 to Present</span>
				</div>

				<div class="exp-list">

					<!-- SLCC -->
					<div class="exp-item">
						<div class="exp-header">
							<div class="exp-header-left">
								<div class="exp-company">SLCC Flooring</div>
								<div class="exp-role-line">
									<span class="exp-role">AI Product Designer</span>
									<span class="exp-type">2026 – Present</span>
								</div>
								<div class="exp-role-line">
									<span class="exp-role">UX Designer (Intern)</span>
									<span class="exp-type exp-type-muted">May 2022 – Dec 2024</span>
								</div>
								<div class="exp-summary">Designing and leading end-to-end AI agent system to automate front-desk operations, including customer inquiry response, inventory lookup, and order processing.</div>
							</div>
							<div class="exp-header-right">
								<div class="exp-toggle">
									<svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none">
										<path d="M5 1v8M1 5h8" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
									</svg>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="exp-body">
							<div class="exp-body-inner">
								<div class="exp-sub-role-header">
									<span class="exp-role">UX Designer (Intern)</span>
									<span class="exp-period">May 2022 – Dec 2024</span>
								</div>
								<div class="exp-bullet">Streamlined B2B buyer decisions with <b>AI-powered recommendations</b> by redesigning the quote request flow into a 3-step process.</div>
								<div class="exp-bullet">Boosted trade show attendance by <b>20%</b> by mapping the retailer journey to optimize promotional material placement and messaging strategy.</div>
								<div class="exp-bullet">Improved product discovery and <b>reduced bounce rate by 35%</b> through user testing and iterative design of the product filtering system.</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- NASA -->
					<div class="exp-item">
						<div class="exp-header">
							<div class="exp-header-left">
								<div class="exp-company">NASA</div>
								<div class="exp-role-line">
									<span class="exp-role">UX Researcher</span>
									<span class="exp-type">Sponsored Research</span>
								</div>
